An Act
ENROLLED HOUSE
BILL NO. 4044 By: Caldwell (Trey), Kane, and
West (Tammy) of the House
and
Hall and Haste of the
Senate
An Act relating to the Oklahoma Office of Educational
Quality and Accountability; appropriating certain
funds in certain amount for certain purpose;
directing utilization of certain amounts for certain
purposes; providing for noncodification; providing an
effective date; and declaring an emergency.
SUBJECT: Oklahoma Office of Educational Quality and
Accountability
BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
There is hereby appropriated to the Office of Educational
Quality and Accountability from any monies not otherwise
appropriated from the General Revenue Fund of the State Treasury for
the fiscal year ending June 30, 2027, the sum of Seven Hundred
Eighty-five Thousand Dollars ($785,000.00) or so much thereof as may
be necessary to perform the duties imposed upon the Office of
Educational Quality and Accountability by law.
SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
Funds appropriated by Section 1 of this act shall be utilized as
follows:

Seven Hundred Eighty-five Thousand Dollars ($785,000.00) to
implement the provisions of Enrolled House Bill No. 4268 of the 2nd
Session of the 60th Oklahoma Legislature.
SECTION 3. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
SECTION 4. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
